caption.text:
The no1 tool I’ve used to build my brand

Do you want to share your knowledge or skills with your followers? But you don’t know how to reach them?

Maybe you have created a “Free Guide” you’d like to share but nobody ever downloads it?

Are you out off building a website because you don’t have the technical skills to take payments or troubleshoot a problem?

Are you trying to build an email list in case you ever lost access to your social media?

Or…perhaps you’d just like to direct people to a specific page on your existing website, without them getting lost along the way clicking into the wrong places 🤪

I hear you!!!!! I wanted all those things too!

I knew I had lots of knowledge about Instagram but I didn’t know how to share that knowledge with people without investing thousands of pounds on a fancy website - and I didn’t have the first idea how to do that!! Until I heard about Stan Store!! @stanforcreators 

For £22 a month I have my own site, I chose its url and I have added all my products, all with separate pages and links. It’s so simple to set up.

I have managed to build an email list, and even track how well my individual posts are doing, so I can create more of what works and ultimately grow my instagram account.

I have been a happily paying customer since I started Embrace and they have now contacted me and asked me to become a brand ambassador!! 🤯🤯 I honestly can’t speak highly enough of them, and I certainly wouldn’t have been able to grow as quickly as I have without Stan.

They have given me a code for a 2 week free trial for any of my followers who’d like to try them out! It literally takes a few minutes to get up and running! comment STAN below, I’ll send you a link, and enjoy 2 weeks free, on me ❤️

Any questions, I’ll try and answer below!
 
#instagramgrowth #instagramforbusiness #smallbusinessowner #smallbusinesssupport

reusable_text_info.text: This is the number one tool I used to grow a 6 figure business from inside my wardrobe

caption.text:
A simple IG story to share your website

This is an oldie but a goodie! Such a creative way of sharing your business or website, you’ll wonder why you didn’t try it sooner! And the bonus you didn’t even need to take a photo! 

Don’t forget to SAVE this post to refer back to!!

Step by step instructions below ⬇️

- tap to open a new instagram story post, click camera and scroll across the bottom of the screen until you get the magnifying glass- type “background phone 1”

- Tap through these backgrounds until you find one you like, take a tap to take photo and save the image

- No go to begin a new story post, and add the background image you just saved

- Now go to your website, your IG page or whatever screen you would like to promote and take a screenshot

- Now go back into instagram, tap your sticker tab and find the link sticker, you can add your website link, or any site you’d like to share by pasting it here 

- Place the link on top of the phone in your IG story 

- Go to your sticker tab again, to your photo album and add the screen shot you took on your phone and resize to fit in the phone on the instagram story 

- Now go to sticker tab again, type “cafezim” and place a coffee gif inside the cup

- Lastly sticker tab one more time and type “tap here” choose the sticker you like best and place on your phone, meaning anyone who taps your phone will be taken to your link you shared!

- I added some text directing audiences to click my phone on screen but you can add any text you wish

This is such a simple but creative way to share a website or link! 

If you’re struggling with what text to use to begin your captions, comment HOOKS and I’ll send over my free 100 hooks and captions to try! 

If you liked this tip, make sure you’re following me, I share new ones daily to help you on your instagram journey! ❤️

caption.text:
Easy 1 photo story ⬇️

This is such a professional and creative filter and you could use if for any kind of instagram post! You could also add a link to shop or visit a website.

I have saved the filter effect bottom of the screen, if you don’t immediately see it.  Go to bottom of screen- you will see message “MADE WITH EFFECT” tap this, filter is inside.

You have to SAVE this post, you don’t want to forget the steps as this is a good one!

- tap and begin a new story,, add any image of your choice, and tap the sparkles button and look for the filter “3R”, if you don’t see this effect you might need to save it first.

- once you have applied the filter, go to your sticker tab, and type in record- choose one of the spinning records and place in the centre of the screen

- Now go to your sticker tab again, and type “new tab new” add the spinning new post sticker and place it on the record 

- Now go to your sticker tab for a third time, your photo album and add the original image. Tap to make it a circle and place in centre of the screen

- Lastly, go to your original image and hold down until you see the shimmer effect and then paste into instagram over the photo you added 

If you need a trending audio, SAVE this post, or look through my previous ones- I use them for all my posts! 

If you liked this instagram story idea, make sure you’re following me, I share new ones daily to help you on your instagram journey! 🚀❤️

I’m going to be removing my 75 minute video lesson from my store soon, so if you had been thinking about getting that, now is the time! Just comment CLASS and I’ll send you a link over to check it out!

reusable_text_info.text: An Instagram story idea, I bet you didn’t know…

caption.text:
Let me help you below ⬇️ 

There is a LOT of noise on social media about what you should or shouldn’t be posting to grow or go viral- forget ALL that- this is your reminder from me that Instagrams no1 priority is to build a community not just getting random viral views.

Forget sales, Make a post today, that will 

*make someone laugh, 
*help with with a problem they have
*remind them of something important (this post is doing just that)

Let me know below what you do, or what you’re going to share, to help you connect today.  Will you try it? if I can help you with an idea I will.  Now, share this post with a friend who needs to hear this today 🫶🏻

After all, Viral content shouldn’t be your priority, you want to find “your people”, you want your people to recognise you as the “go to” person in your niche. You do that by connecting. Let’s chat below ⬇️ 

#instagramgrowth #igtips #instagramstrategy #contentstrategy #contentcreator #smallbusinessuk #smallbusinessowner

music_asset_info.title: Memories

text_info_list.text: Instead on aiming for your content to go viral when you post today
Aim to make someone smile, or teach them one simple tip or remind them of a simple fact in your niche ⬇️

caption.text:
I know it sounds simple, and that’s because it is- when you have a strategy to follow,

Be honest with me, 

- Do you know your Niche
- Do your posts have a purpose
- Do you know the problem you solve
- Do you know who you’re talking to 

Trying to grow without knowing these things is like driving on a road to nowhere!

Let me know the answers to these below! I’d love to know your account outcome, and audiences! 

#instagramgrowthexpert 

PS - Comment “GUIDE” and I’ll send over a link to my growth guide to use my strategy 

#instagramgrowth #iggrowth #smallbusinessowner #mumsinbusiness #iggrowthtips

caption.text:
Simple Hack to Share a Reel ⬇️

Instagram has confirmed that reels are the still the no1 way to reach new audiences, but stories are the best way to connect to audiences….well this hack combines both!!

Don’t forget to SAVE this post so you don’t forget the steps!! 

- tap and begin a new reel, add any image you’d like to showcase, and go to your sparkles tab. Look for the “filter BW Half. window” take a screenshot and close image.

- Now go to any reel or post you’d like to share, tap the airplane button and share to your story. 

- Go to your sticker tab, your photo album and add the image you just created, fill the screen with it, then hold down and slide down to bring the reel you shared forwards and send the image back one layer.

- Resize the reel so it fits nicely onto the frame on the right hand side, go to your sticker tab, and type “new reel black” add the sticker I’ve used and go to sticker tab one last time to add a click icon.

- lastly, add some text to explain your post!

Now anyone that clicks that reel gets taken straight through to watch it. 

If you love this instagram reel idea, check out some of my others and make sure you’re following me, I share new ones every single day to help you on your instagram growth journey!

But remember if you want some more detailed help on how to grow your Instagram audience, comment GUIDE below and I’ll send over a link to the strategy I wrote myself which has gained me 76,000 followers in the last 30 days 🚀

reusable_text_info.text: An Instagram secret, I bet you didn’t know

caption.text:
The truth is ⬇️

Strategy…I know, We are all just trying our best, you will often find me writing emails from the football sideline, or working from inside my car!

That busy life juggle happens to us all, going to work, seeing family, catching up with friends, trying to get to the gym, AND figuring out this algorithm…but what if I could at least take away the pressure of what to post on instagram? 

I wrote a 53 page guide, with the exact process I use to come up with content ideas, and grow my account to over 400,000 followers this year!

Comment GUIDE and I’ll whiz that link over, so that’s one thing off the list for now!

#iggrowth #instagramgrowth #contentstrategy #smallbusinesslife #contentideas #igtips

text_info_list.text: I know how the juggle feels, you’re busy, Instagram sometimes becomes the last item on your list, but I am here to help that feel easier for you 🫶🏻 ⬇️
nobody talks about how hard it is trying to fit running a business around everything else you have to do in “real life” with kids, family and work

caption.text:
Work from home they said…

Share if you relate 🤣 I know I’m not the only one who feels this, you’re short on time with a list of jobs as long as your arm, you’re trying to get all of the things done - quickly, and around your family so you can actually be present, spend lazy Saturday mornings watching TV and eating croissants, and not stressing what you post next on Instagram.

Be honest, Will I find you huddled in a quiet spot trying to actually plan ahead - but the everyone is home…their space is their space and your space is their space too, might be the dogs, might be the kids but working at home is no simple task!

If you want to spend less time weekend working at home, and more time focusing on your family or doing things that you enjoy, you’ll want to hear about the “Embrace your instagram course I have coming up”  just comment the word REGISTER below to join the waitlist and hear about my October launch

#instagramgrowthhacks #instagramgrowthtip #instagramgrowth #iggrowth #contentstrategy #smallbusinessowner #socialmediahelp

caption.text:
Increase watch time ⬇️

instagram has confirmed that watch time is one the metrics they measure when calculating engagement on your account! Increase your watch time, can directly increase your reach, try this with this simple reveal effect! 

Don’t forget to SAVE this post so you don’t forget the steps ⬇️

- tap and begin a new post, choose any image you would like to share and resize it where you’d like on the page.

- go to your pen tool, and colour pick a colour on screen, I’m using the sheer highlighter brush, but the solid colour would work too! Hold down and colour the whole screen.

- now go to your sticker tab, type in “Polaroid frame” choose your favourite one, and place over the space the image is occupying 

- go to your pen tool again, select the eraser pen, make it slightly larger. Now go to your screen record option on your phone. Start the recording and erase the colour from the centre of the photo frame. Once the colour is gone, stop the recording and close this post.

- begin a new story and add this recording you just made. Now you can add any text, stickers or link that you wish. 

Now you have your design covered, if you want to work on your strategy too, comment the word GUIDE below! I’ll share my step by step strategy to how I’ve grown 400k in 2024! 

#instagramgrowth #instagramforbusiness #instagramtips #storyideas #contentcreator

reusable_text_info.text: An Instagram secret, I bet you didn’t know…

caption.text:
Stop shooting boring video!

Having a video with movement in is key to stop your audience from scrolling by, we call this a visual hook and it’s key to success on Instagram.

Now, here is the most simple hack to allow you to capture your hands, in an interesting shot to keep your audience watching and best of all no fancy equipment required! 

Use this tip for interesting angles, detail shots, or simply cut into your regular style content 

- take your phone out of its phone case, place the case under your shirt and put the phone back inside the case so now the fabric is sandwiched in between the phone and the case.

- shooting from this angle allows your hands to be captured clearly in shot.

- completing any task with your hand visible, 
making something, 
doing something, 
writing something 
these would all work as great visual hooks to stop the scroll.

Adding movement makes your videos more visually engaging increasing watching time and hopefully reach!

If you enjoyed this tip, make sure you’re following me! I share new tips daily to make your instagram growth journey that bit easier!

Did you know about this tip? If you feel you need help with your Instagram strategy, comment GUIDE, and I will whiz over the link to my Instagram growth guide!

#instagramstrategy #contentcreator #iggrowth #smallbusinesslife #smallbusinessuk #iggrowth

caption.text:
This changed everything for me…

TELL don’t just Sell 

Your audience wants to know how they’ll feel when they buy the thing you offer, getting specific into the outcome you offer helps them to relate. Using this proven prompt, spell out that feeling.

The person who sent you this wants you to…

Examples ⬇️ 

“The person who sent you this, wants you to, stop stressing about hashtags and actually grow an engaged an committed community on Instagram”

“The person you sent you this, wants to watch Harry Potter boxsets and light our new pumpkin spice candle with you this Halloween”

“The person who sent you this, has just found out how to get budget friendly family dinners on the table in 15 minutes or less”

PS - Comment “Waitlist ” and I’ll send you the link to my new course launching in October. This is going to be like having me, as your business partner and in your pocket! Demystifying Instagram and breaking it all down so you will love showing up for your brand!

Have a go below ⬇️

#iggrowth #instagramgrowth #instagramstrategy #contentcreator #contentstrategy
